<paragraph blockId="11.[170,775,235,821]" pageId="11" pageNumber="3201">Morphometry: (length in mm). Female: Body 45.55, Tegmina, 36.0, Hind femur, 20.7, Pronotum 9.6.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[170,775,235,821]" pageId="11" pageNumber="3201">
Remarks: This species can be easily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[238,633,646,673]" class="Insecta" family="Baissogryllidae" genus="Oedipoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="3201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coerulescens">
<emphasis box="[238,423,646,672]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="3201">O. coerulescens</emphasis>
(Linnaeus, 1758)
</taxonomicName>
because its wings are basally red.
</paragraph>
